glossary.definition: Global parameters controlling dates, account configuration, and bar size.
Section that defines derived series or imported references available to strategies.
Block containing trading rules, universe, sizing, and entry/exit logic for one approach.
Reusable formulas or helper items shared across strategies.
Boolean condition required before a candidate symbol can be considered for entry.
Ranking metric applied to qualified symbols to determine trade priority.
Condition that, when true, blocks new entries (e.g., during market drawdowns).
Boolean condition that, when true, triggers exit orders.
Protective stop price formula applied to open positions.
Directive that specifies which symbols or symbol lists to include in a test.
Setting that chooses the timeframe aggregation (Daily, Weekly, Monthly, etc.).
Function for referencing data from alternate symbols or bar sizes inside formulas.
Cap on the number of simultaneous positions a strategy may open.
Specification describing which symbols a strategy trades.
Expression that sets the sizing of new entries (shares or dollars).
Built-in series tracking cumulative equity for the current strategy.
